OL,3,CNewcastle's Eddie Howe urges FA not to
OL,4,C'throw the book' at suspended Tonali
OL,6,FWhen asked if he was worried Tonali,
OL,7,Fwho cost around #60million to sign
OL,8,Fcould be handed a consecutive ban to
OL,9,Frun after the existing penalty has
OL,10,Fcome to an end, Howe said: "We don't
OL,11,Fknow, is the honest answer. I
OL,12,Fcertainly hope for Sandro that there
OL,13,Fare no further consequences.
OL,15,F"He has suffered during this period,
OL,16,Fhe has sought help, he's been very
OL,17,Fhonest, he has admitted he has an
OL,18,Fissue, and I think the best thing for
OL,19,FSandro would be to resume his career
OL,20,Fhaving taken his punishment and having
OL,21,Flearned a lot of lessons from this."
